Package gw.api.web.aria

Enum Class AriaRole

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<AriaRole>
gw.api.web.aria.AriaRole
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<AriaRole>, Constable
public enum AriaRole extends Enum<AriaRole>
This is essentially an export of WAI-ARIA current guidelines, with deprecated options removed. Aria roles are used to inform screen readers, and help with navigation. They are added via the role attribute. id
Many native HTML essentially already represent a given aria role. Like "textbox" is handled the same was as a native textarea element, so there would be no reason to add a role to it, but it also would not cause conflict either. It's important to remember that our widgets, even something as simple as a textbox, all consist of nested elements. Almost every widget is a div wrapper, with more div wrappers, and then eventually something like a textarea inside. By default, aria roles that come from PCFs are meant to be "overrides", or "additional" information, but we don't limit a user from adding a progressbar aria role to our textarea value widget. One day we could, but for now, it's safer to just allow all the attributes to pass through and not try to be too smart about it.
